Popular musician David Adeleke also known as Davido has fulfilled his promise to donate N250m to orphanage homes in Nigeria. Davido had in November 2021 asked his friends and colleagues to donate one million Naira each for an N100m target. He however received N200m from friends and colleagues in the industry added N50m, making it 250m, and disclosed that the money would be donated to orphanages in Nigeria. In a statement on his Instagram page, Davido has given an update, displaying a receipt of successful transactions to 292 orphanages in all the States in Nigeria. Chimamanda Adichie Finally Reveals The Priest Who Criticized Her… IPOB Sit-at-Home Records Compliance In Ebonyi Part of the statement read: “I bring you an update as promised. Since its inauguration, the members of the committee have worked tirelessly to ensure that they collate the names and information of the documented and verified orphanages. “So far, the total of N250m has been disbursed to 292 orphanages. “I thought it wise to give you my loyal fans, friends, and family an update in this regard.“Thank you to everyone who made this possible. Thank you for your continuous support and prayer. “Always remember, we rise by lifting others.” Fans took to social media, applauding Davido for fulfilling his promise and helping orphans across the country. POLL